      _TV Show Notes_ 
      ===============----------------------------------------------------
                                   
       Highlights of England's opening game in the 2008 Rugby League 
       World Cup in Townsville, Australia.

       The first World Cup was held back in 1951, but there have only 
       been 11 tournaments since, the last of which was eight years ago.
       Hosts Australia have lifted the World Cup nine times and will be 
       favourites to triumph once again. England, who are under the 
       stewardship of Australian-born Tony Smith, will hope to at least 
       reach the final. Many of their squad were part of the Great Britain 
       team that beat New Zealand in the Test series in 2007, and star 
       players are likely to include captain Jamie Peacock and 
       newly-crowned Man of Steel James Graham.

       There are also highlights of Australia's first match of the 
       tournament, against old rivals New Zealand, whom they beat in the
       2000 World Cup final at Old Trafford.

       Coverage is presented by Dave Woods, with studio guests Ian 
       Millward and former Great Britain head coach Brian Noble.

